descript.abstract: The Street Network Database (SND) is a representation of the physical, land based, improved, travel pathway infrastructure and associated theoretical address ranges. The pathway representation consists of Segments and Intersection elements. A Segment is a linear graphic element that represents a continuous physical travel path terminated by path end (dead end) or physical intersection with other travel paths. Segments have one streetname, one address range and one set of segment characteristics. A Segment may have none or multiple alias streetnames. Segment types included are Freeways, Highways, Streets, Alleys (named only), Railroads, Walkways, and Bikelanes. SNDSEG is a linear feature class representing the SND Segment Feature, with attributes for Streetname, Address Range, Alias Streetname and segment Characteristics objects. Part of the Address Range and all of Streetname objects are logically shared with the Discrete Address Point-Master Address File layer.
descript.purpose: Cartography - Used to depict the City's transportation network location and connections, typically on smaller scaled maps or images where a single line representation is appropriate. Used to depict specific classifications of roadway use, also typically at smaller scales. Used to label transportation network feature names typically on larger scaled maps. Used to label address ranges with associated transportation network features typically on larger scaled maps. Geocode reference - Used as a source for derived reference data for address validation and theoretical address location Address Range data repository - This data store is the City's address range repository defining address ranges in association with transportation network features. Polygon boundary reference - Used to define various area boundaries is other feature classes where coincident with the transportation network. Does not contain polygon features. Address based extracts - Used to create flat-file extracts typically indexed by address with reference to business data typically associated with transportation network features. Thematic linear location reference. - By providing unique, stable identifiers for each linear feature, thematic data is associated to specific transportation network features via these identifiers. Thematic intersection location reference - By providing unique, stable identifiers for each intersection feature, thematic data is associated to specific transportation network features via these identifiers. Network route tracing - Used as source for derived reference data used to determine point to point travel paths or determine optimal stop allocation along a travel path. Topological connections with segments - Used to provide a specific definition of location for each transportation network feature. Also provides a specific definition of connection between each transportation network feature. (defines where the streets are and the relationship between them ie. 4th Ave is west of 5th Ave and 4th Ave does intersect with Cherry St) Event location reference - Used as source for derived reference data used to locate event and linear referencing.

attr.attrdef: From Physical Intersection Identifier. Segment starting endpoint (from node) ID. The identifier of the physical intersection that defines the start of a line feature. See SNDINTR feature class INTR-ID.

To Physical Intersection Identifier. Segment completion endpoint (to node) ID. The identifier of the physical intersection that defines the end of a line feature. See SNDINTR feature class attribute INTR-ID.
Segment Identifier. Unique identifier for segments. Value will be stable over lifecycle of feature in the database.

GeoBasys database Segment Identifier. A concatenated 5 digit 'on street' number and 4 digit 'street sequence' number from the SDOT GeoBasys database. Only applies to City of Seattle ROWs Values assigned by SDOT.
Within City Limits Condition Flag. Attribute to flag SND arc elements which are inside or along the City of Seattle Boundary from arc elements outside the City limits
Left To Address. The left-side theoretical high address number along a line segment. Side is dependant upon segment geometry orientation.
Right To Address. The right-side theoretical high address number along a line segment. Side is dependant upon segment geometry orientation.
Streetname Identifier. Foreign key to STNAME table.
Left Zip Code Identifier. Foreign key to CityStateZip table. Provides Postal Zip Code for addresses on the 'left' side of a segment.
Right Zip Code Identifier. Foreign key to CityStateZip table. Provides Postal Zip Code for addresses on the 'right' side of a segment.

SND Street Code. The street code designation for all SND line segments. Because the SND is derived from a "right-of-way" file, there are many varieties of both streets and non-streets. Based upon SND interpretation of segment function, ownership and modal accessibility as classed in ST.CODE domain.
Arterial Classification Code. The arterial classification code for all SND line segments. Arterial classification values assigned by SDOT, based upon SDOT classifications.
Bicycle Route Code. The bicycle route code for all SND line segments. values assigned by SDOT, based upon SDOT classifications.
Transit Route Code. The transit use code for all SND line segments. values assigned by SDOT, based upon SDOT classifications.
Snow and Ice Response Routes Code. Coding representing Seattle Department of Transportation (SDOT) priority response routes for Snow and Ice removal.
Non-Street Code. A code scheme used to differentiate and classify segments representing drivable streets vs. 'other' non-drivable conditions.
SDOT Hansen database requirement. Hansen internal number through which the link to the Hansen database is maintained for all congruous features.
SDOT Hansen database requirement. An attribute that differentiates asset type in the Hansen database.
SDOT Hansen database requirement. The name (in Hansen database) of the from-node of a linear asset. See Intersection feature UNITID attribute.
SDOT Hansen database requirement. The name (In Hansen Database) of the to-node of a linear asset. See Intersection feature UNITID attribute.
Feature geometry.

horizpa.horizpar: Where applicable (open public streets), street (line) is within its associated ROW boundary. · Where street is not within a ROW, street (line) is within the pavement shown on most recent positionally accurate orthophoto layer. Certain intersections are generalized as a better representation of traffic flow patterns. Vertically "stacked" streets are offset to allow two-dimensional graphic representation.
